4_12	0.16666666666666666	Diagnosing psychiatric conditions is more of an art than a science, and the Not Otherwise Specified label reflects the imprecision of that art.
4_13	0.10526315789473684	The American Psychiatric Association's manual has a Not Otherwise Specified category for many disorders, whenever symptoms are so vague, so mild or so untreatable that it doesn't seem to warrant the full-fledged diagnosis.
4_14	0.15384615384615385	With the manual continually under revision, the Not Otherwise Specified grab bag is the place where new diagnoses emerge.
4_15	0.15789473684210525	For instance, the diagnosis of Asperger's syndrome, a variant of autism, was pulled from a collection of disorders previously labeled Pervasive Personality Disorder Not Otherwise Specified.
4_16	0.0	Much is at stake in whether a condition is elevated to the status of a full-fledged diagnosis.
4_17	0.0	Because no laboratory tests or other objective criteria exist for making psychiatric diagnoses, the American Psychiatric Association's manual is the definitive arbiter of the line between normal and abnormal.
4_18	0.0	Its definitions help determine such practical matters as insurance reimbursement, competence and eligibility for disability.
4_19	0.16666666666666666	But they also help determine something more elusive, and probably more important: whether someone's behavior should be considered a personality quirk or a symptom of mental illness.
