8_1	0.1111111111111111	CREDIT: Robert Holst/NYTRNG (with sidebar 2BINGEEATING) Binge eating gets a closer look New study tests drug that curbs overeaters' urge
8_2	0.15384615384615385	The temptation to overeat will strike most of us during the holiday season, but for those who suffer from a binge-eating disorder, holiday feasting can be self-inflicted hell.
8_3	0.9	Binge eating disorder is a newly recognized condition that probably affects millions of Americans.
8_4	0.09090909090909091	Those with the disorder frequently eat large amounts of food while feeling at a loss to control their eating.
8_5	0.125	To date, there are no approved medications to treat binge-eating disorder, but a large, multi-center study may offer hope to the 2 percent of the population who suffer from it.
8_6	0.08333333333333333	Dr. Nathan Shapira, an assistant professor of psychiatry of the University of Florida's College of Medicine, is among the researchers testing the effectiveness of topiramate, a drug developed to treat the convulsions and seizures of epilepsy, in controlling binge eating.
8_7	0.0	Shapira said that when topiramate was used for epilepsy patients, many reported that they also had a marked decrease in appetite and even lost weight.
8_8	0.5333333333333333	A small study of some 60 patients with binge eating disorder showed that those who received the topiramate rather than a placebo binged less often and also lost weight.
8_9	0.0	The new study will test the effectiveness of topiramate in 350 binge eaters from around the country, Shapira said.
8_10	0.0	Results are anticipated next year.
8_11	0.0	It is funded by Ortho McNeil Pharmaceutical, which makes the drug.
8_12	0.6153846153846154	Binge eating disorder, Shapira emphasizes, is not the same as indulging in an occasional binge at the table or "grazing" through an array of buffet offerings.
8_13	0.0	"Everyone probably binges at some point, particularly during 'sanctioned' events like Thanksgiving dinner," Shapira said.
8_14	0.35714285714285715	"The real difference between 'grazing' and binge eating is eating much more than normal in a short period of time, often less than two hours.
8_15	0.0	"It's a terrible situation to be surrounded by food when that's all that you are thinking about," he said.
8_16	0.0	After a binge, he said, binge eaters feel disgusted with themselves.
8_17	0.0	As a result, they often eat alone or very rapidly, and will eat until they are uncomfortably full.
8_18	0.5333333333333333	Unlike eating disorders such as bulimia nervosa or anorexia where victims are predominantly female, the ratio of female to male binge eaters is about 3-to-2.
8_19	0.0	It is common in all ethnic groups.
8_20	1.0	Almost all who have this disorder are either overweight or obese.
8_21	0.25	It has been estimated that up to 30 percent of those in weight-loss programs have a binge-eating disorder.
8_22	0.0	They usually develop a weight problem earlier in life and do not do as well in these programs.
8_23	0.6666666666666666	One study looking at Overeaters Anonymous found that 70 percent of the members had a binge eating disorder, Shapira said.
8_24	0.8888888888888888	The major complications of binge eating disorder are the diseases that accompany obesity.
8_25	0.15384615384615385	These include diabetes, high blood pressure, high cholesterol levels, gallbladder disease, heart disease and certain types of cancer.
8_26	0.7272727272727273	The causes of the disorder are still unknown, but up to half of all people with binge eating disorder have a history of depression.
